  <!-- ========== SECTION 07: DATABASE TOOLS ========== -->
  <section id="database-tools" class="ess-section" aria-label="Database management tools">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ess-section__header">
        <span class="ess-section__number">07</span>
        <h2 class="ess-section__title">Database Management Tools</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="ess-section__intro">Working with databases requires tools for querying, schema visualization, and data manipulation. GUI clients make complex operations more accessible and reduce the risk of destructive mistakes.</p>

      <!-- ===== DBeaver ===== -->
      <article class="ess-tool" id="dbeaver">
        <div class="ess-tool__header">
          <div class="ess-tool__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"></ellipse><path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3"></path><path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="ess-tool__title-wrap">
            <h3 class="ess-tool__name">DBeaver</h3>
            <p class="ess-tool__tagline">Universal database client supporting dozens of databases</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__tags">
          <span class="tag tag-free">Community Edition</span>
          <span class="tag tag-paid">Pro $10/mo</span>
          <span class="tag">Windows</span>
          <span class="tag">macOS</span>
          <span class="tag">Linux</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__body">
          <p>DBeaver connects to virtually any database: PostgreSQL, MySQL, Oracle, MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis, and dozens more. The unified interface means learning one tool works across different databases. SQL editor includes auto-completion, syntax highlighting, and execution history.</p>
          <p>Schema visualization shows relationships between tables. Data editing happens in spreadsheet-like grids with inline validation. Query results can be exported to CSV, JSON, or other formats. The free Community Edition covers most needs; Pro adds NoSQL databases and cloud storage support.</p>

          <div class="ess-tool__pros-cons">
            <div class="ess-tool__pros">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--pros">Pros</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Supports almost any database</li>
                <li>Free version very capable</li>
                <li>ERD generation and visualization</li>
                <li>Cross-platform availability</li>
                <li>Active development</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="ess-tool__cons">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--cons">Cons</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Interface can feel cluttered</li>
                <li>Java-based, heavier resource usage</li>
                <li>Learning curve for advanced features</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="ess-tool__alternatives">
            <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle">Alternatives to Consider</h4>
            <div class="ess-tool__alt-grid">
              <div class="ess-tool__alt-card">
                <strong>pgAdmin</strong>
                <p>Official PostgreSQL client. Free and open source. PostgreSQL-specific features more polished than universal clients.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="ess-tool__alt-card">
                <strong>MongoDB Compass</strong>
                <p>Official MongoDB GUI. Visual query builder, aggregation pipeline builder. Free. Essential for MongoDB development.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 08: API CLIENTS ========== -->
  <section id="api-clients" class="ess-section" aria-label="API testing clients">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ess-section__header">
        <span class="ess-section__number">08</span>
        <h2 class="ess-section__title">API Testing Clients</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="ess-section__intro">APIs drive modern applications. Testing endpoints, debugging responses, and documenting APIs require specialized tools that go beyond browser dev tools or curl commands.</p>

      <!-- ===== Postman ===== -->
      <article class="ess-tool" id="postman">
        <div class="ess-tool__header">
          <div class="ess-tool__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-6.219-8.56"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="ess-tool__title-wrap">
            <h3 class="ess-tool__name">Postman</h3>
            <p class="ess-tool__tagline">Comprehensive API development platform</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__tags">
          <span class="tag tag-free">Free Tier</span>
          <span class="tag tag-paid">$12-29/user/mo</span>
          <span class="tag">Windows</span>
          <span class="tag">macOS</span>
          <span class="tag">Linux</span>
          <span class="tag">Web</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__body">
          <p>Postman has evolved from simple API client to full development platform. Collections organize related requests. Environments switch between development, staging, and production with variable substitution. Pre-request scripts and tests enable automation with JavaScript.</p>
          <p>Mock servers simulate APIs during frontend development. Documentation generation creates shareable API references from collections. Team collaboration features include shared workspaces and version control. The Newman CLI runs collections in CI/CD pipelines for API testing.</p>

          <div class="ess-tool__pros-cons">
            <div class="ess-tool__pros">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--pros">Pros</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Full-featured API development platform</li>
                <li>Excellent documentation generation</li>
                <li>Team collaboration features</li>
                <li>Mock server capabilities</li>
                <li>Extensive testing framework</li>
                <li>Free tier suitable for individuals</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="ess-tool__cons">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--cons">Cons</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Can feel bloated for simple testing</li>
                <li>Requires account for syncing</li>
                <li>Paid features necessary for teams</li>
                <li>Resource heavy</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="ess-tool__alternatives">
            <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle">Alternatives to Consider</h4>
            <div class="ess-tool__alt-grid">
              <div class="ess-tool__alt-card">
                <strong>Insomnia</strong>
                <p>Simpler API client with cleaner interface. Good GraphQL support. Free with optional paid sync. Lighter weight than Postman.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="ess-tool__alt-card">
                <strong>Hoppscotch</strong>
                <p>Open source, web-based API client. No installation required. Free. Good for quick testing without local software.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 09: PACKAGE MANAGERS ========== -->
  <section id="package-managers" class="ess-section" aria-label="Package managers">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ess-section__header">
        <span class="ess-section__number">09</span>
        <h2 class="ess-section__title">Package Managers</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="ess-section__intro">Package managers automate software installation, updates, and dependency resolution. They're essential infrastructure for development environments, enabling reproducible setups and easy tooling management.</p>

      <!-- ===== npm ===== -->
      <article class="ess-tool" id="npm">
        <div class="ess-tool__header">
          <div class="ess-tool__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="ess-tool__title-wrap">
            <h3 class="ess-tool__name">npm (Node Package Manager)</h3>
            <p class="ess-tool__tagline">JavaScript ecosystem package manager</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__tags">
          <span class="tag tag-free">Free</span>
          <span class="tag tag-oss">Open Source</span>
          <span class="tag">Windows</span>
          <span class="tag">macOS</span>
          <span class="tag">Linux</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__body">
          <p>npm manages JavaScript packages for Node.js and frontend projects. The registry contains over 1.5 million packages covering every conceivable need. Package.json declares dependencies with semantic versioning. Lock files ensure consistent installations across machines and time.</p>
          <p>Scripts in package.json automate common tasks: testing, building, linting. npm run becomes the universal interface for project commands. For JavaScript developers, npm is unavoidable infrastructure.</p>

          <div class="ess-tool__pros-cons">
            <div class="ess-tool__pros">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--pros">Pros</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Massive package ecosystem</li>
                <li>Standard for JavaScript development</li>
                <li>Script running built-in</li>
                <li>Free and ubiquitous</li>
                <li>Security audit tools included</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="ess-tool__cons">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--cons">Cons</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Can be slow with large dependency trees</li>
                <li>Node_modules size becomes huge</li>
                <li>Version conflicts require manual resolution</li>
                <li>Security issues in packages common</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="ess-tool__alternatives">
            <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle">Alternatives to Consider</h4>
            <div class="ess-tool__alt-grid">
              <div class="ess-tool__alt-card">
                <strong>Yarn</strong>
                <p>Facebook's alternative to npm. Faster installs, better monorepo support. Compatible with npm registry.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="ess-tool__alt-card">
                <strong>pnpm</strong>
                <p>Efficient package manager using hard links to save disk space. Much faster and smaller than npm. Growing adoption.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- ===== pip ===== -->
      <article class="ess-tool" id="pip">
        <div class="ess-tool__header">
          <div class="ess-tool__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"></path><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="ess-tool__title-wrap">
            <h3 class="ess-tool__name">pip (Python Package Installer)</h3>
            <p class="ess-tool__tagline">Python's package management system</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__tags">
          <span class="tag tag-free">Free</span>
          <span class="tag tag-oss">Open Source</span>
          <span class="tag">Windows</span>
          <span class="tag">macOS</span>
          <span class="tag">Linux</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__body">
          <p>pip installs Python packages from PyPI (Python Package Index). Virtual environments isolate project dependencies, preventing conflicts between projects requiring different package versions. Requirements.txt files declare dependencies for reproducible environments.</p>

          <div class="ess-tool__pros-cons">
            <div class="ess-tool__pros">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--pros">Pros</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Standard Python package manager</li>
                <li>Simple to use</li>
                <li>Vast package ecosystem</li>
                <li>Built into Python</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="ess-tool__cons">
