          <span class="tag tag-oss">Open Source</span>
          <span class="tag">Windows</span>
          <span class="tag">macOS</span>
          <span class="tag">Linux</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ess-tool__body">
          <p>Sphinx powers the official Python documentation and uses reStructuredText markup language. Autodoc extensions extract documentation from Python docstrings automatically. Multiple output formats: HTML, PDF, ePub, man pages, and more from the same source.</p>

          <div class="ess-tool__pros-cons">
            <div class="ess-tool__pros">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--pros">Pros</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Industry standard for Python documentation</li>
                <li>Powerful cross-referencing</li>
                <li>Professional-quality output</li>
                <li>Read the Docs integration</li>
                <li>Multiple output formats</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="ess-tool__cons">
              <h4 class="ess-tool__subtitle ess-tool__subtitle--cons">Cons</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Steeper learning curve than Markdown tools</li>
                <li>ReStructuredText more complex</li>
                <li>Best suited for Python projects</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- ===== JSDoc ===== -->
